---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-explained', text: 'How Multi-Country Works', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Plan Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'area-coverage', text: 'Area of Coverage Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'considerations', text: 'Key Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Remote Worker Insurance', href: '/best/remote-worker-insurance' },
  { title: 'Digital Nomad Insurance', href: '/best/digital-nomad-insurance' },
  { title: 'Short-Term Insurance', href: '/best/short-term-expat-insurance' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Changing Countries Guide', href: '/guides/changing-countries' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Global Coverage' },
  { key: 'flexibility', header: 'Move Flexibility' },
  { key: 'regionOptions', header: 'Region Options' },
  { key: 'priceRange', header: 'Price Range' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', coverage: 'Worldwide', flexibility: 'Excellent', regionOptions: 'Multiple', priceRange: '$200-600/mo' },
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', coverage: 'Worldwide', flexibility: 'Excellent', regionOptions: 'Multiple', priceRange: '$300-800/mo' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', coverage: 'Worldwide', flexibility: 'Good', regionOptions: 'Limited', priceRange: '$180-500/mo' },
  { provider: 'SafetyWing', coverage: '180+ countries', flexibility: 'Excellent', regionOptions: 'Single tier', priceRange: '$45-85/mo' },
  { provider: 'IMG Global', coverage: 'Worldwide', flexibility: 'Good', regionOptions: 'Multiple', priceRange: '$100-300/mo' },
];

const areaColumns = [
  { key: 'area', header: 'Area' },
  { key: 'includes', header: 'Includes' },
  { key: 'priceImpact', header: 'Price Impact' },
  { key: 'bestFor', header: 'Best For' },
];

const areaRows = [
  { area: 'Worldwide excluding US', includes: 'All countries except USA', priceImpact: 'Baseline', bestFor: 'Most expats' },
  { area: 'Worldwide including US', includes: 'All countries', priceImpact: '+50-100%', bestFor: 'US visitors' },
  { area: 'Europe only', includes: 'EU/EEA countries', priceImpact: '-20-30%', bestFor: 'Europe-based expats' },
  { area: 'Asia Pacific', includes: 'Asia and Australia', priceImpact: 'Varies', bestFor: 'Asia-based expats' },
  { area: 'Americas (ex US)', includes: 'Latin America, Canada', priceImpact: 'Varies', bestFor: 'Americas expats' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Multi-Country Expat Insurance 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance for expats who move between countries. Find flexible coverage that works across multiple destinations."
  headline="Best Multi-Country Expat Insurance"
  subheadline="Moving between countries? Working remotely from different locations? You need insurance that follows you anywhere. Here are the most flexible options."
  heroImage="/images/answers/best-multi-country-insurance.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  showHeroCta={false}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Plans"
  ctaButtonHref="/compare/"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Top Picks for Multi-Country Coverage</h2>
  <p>
    These insurers offer the best flexibility for expats who move around:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🌐</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Global Flexibility</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-700 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Seamless coverage across countries. Change your primary country of residence without changing plans.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">👑</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Premium Multi-Country</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Any hospital worldwide, unlimited coverage. Perfect for frequent movers who want no compromises.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">💰</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Budget Multi-Country</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">SafetyWing</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">180+ countries at $45/month. Designed for nomads who change locations constantly.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">⚖️</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Value Full Health</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">IMG Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Full health insurance with good global flexibility at moderate prices.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="coverage-explained">How Multi-Country Coverage Works</h2>
  <p>
    International health insurance for multi-country expats differs from single-country coverage:
  </p>

  <h3>Area of Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    When you buy international health insurance, you select an "area of coverage":
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Worldwide:</strong> Covered in any country</li>
    <li><strong>Worldwide excluding US:</strong> Any country except America</li>
    <li><strong>Regional:</strong> Europe, Asia-Pacific, or Americas only</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Within your area, you can move freely between countries without notifying your insurer or changing your plan.
  </p>

  <h3>Primary Country of Residence</h3>
  <p>
    Most insurers ask for your primary country of residence:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>This is where you spend most of your time</li>
    <li>May affect pricing (costs vary by country)</li>
    <li>You can change it—usually at renewal</li>
    <li>Some plans are more flexible than others</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>True Global vs Regional</h3>
  <p>
    Consider whether you need:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>True global:</strong> You might live anywhere in the world</li>
    <li><strong>Regional:</strong> You'll stay within one region (Europe, Asia, etc.)</li>
    <li>Regional coverage is cheaper if you won't leave the region</li>
    <li>Global coverage gives maximum flexibility</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Multi-Country Plans"
    description="Find coverage that follows you wherever you go."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Multi-Country Plan Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Cigna Global — Best Global Flexibility</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global excels at handling expats who move between countries frequently.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Seamless coverage across 200+ countries</li>
    <li>Easy to change primary country of residence</li>
    <li>Extensive global network</li>
    <li>Direct billing available in most countries</li>
    <li>Telemedicine works worldwide</li>
    <li>Multiple area options (worldwide, regional)</li>
    <li>Excellent claims processing internationally</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Premium pricing. Changing to/from US coverage affects premiums significantly. May need to notify for extended stays in some countries.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/cigna-global">Read our full Cigna Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Bupa Global — Best Premium Multi-Country</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global offers the most flexible premium coverage—any hospital, any country.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Any hospital worldwide—no network restrictions</li>
    <li>Unlimited coverage on top plans</li>
    <li>Complete location flexibility</li>
    <li>Dedicated advisor regardless of location</li>
    <li>Direct billing at major hospitals globally</li>
    <li>No primary residence restrictions</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Most expensive option. May be overkill if you don't need unlimited/any-hospital. Premium for the freedom.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/bupa-global">Read our full Bupa Global review</a></p>

  <h3>SafetyWing — Best Budget Multi-Country</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing was designed for digital nomads who change locations constantly.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>180+ countries covered</li>
    <li>Starts at just $45/month</li>
    <li>No primary residence requirement</li>
    <li>Monthly billing, cancel anytime</li>
    <li>Designed for location-independent lifestyle</li>
    <li>Simple global coverage—no region restrictions</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Travel medical insurance only—not full health. Pre-existing conditions excluded. Limited coverage compared to full plans. Basic network.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/safetywing">Read our full SafetyWing review</a></p>

  <h3>IMG Global — Best Value Full Health</h3>
  <p>
    IMG offers full health insurance with global flexibility at more moderate prices.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Full health insurance coverage</li>
    <li>Global coverage options</li>
    <li>More affordable than Cigna/Bupa</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions after waiting period</li>
    <li>Flexibility to change countries</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Network not as extensive. Claims may be slower. Service level below premium insurers.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/img-global">Read our full IMG Global review</a></p>

  <h2 id="area-coverage">Area of Coverage Options</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={areaColumns} rows={areaRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Choosing Your Area</h3>

  <h4>Worldwide Excluding US</h4>
  <p>
    The most popular choice for expats:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Covers everywhere except the United States</li>
    <li>Most affordable global option</li>
    <li>Works if you have no US connection</li>
    <li>Can add US later (affects price)</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Worldwide Including US</h4>
  <p>
    For expats who need US access:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Covers literally everywhere</li>
    <li>50-100% more expensive than excluding US</li>
    <li>Worth it if you visit or may live in US</li>
    <li>Important for US citizens</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Regional Coverage</h4>
  <p>
    If you'll stay in one region:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Europe-only is popular for EU-based expats</li>
    <li>Asia-Pacific for those in Asia/Australia</li>
    <li>Americas (excluding US) for Latin America</li>
    <li>20-30% savings vs worldwide</li>
    <li>Still covers multiple countries within region</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Choose Your Coverage Area"
    description="Balance flexibility with cost based on where you'll actually be."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
  />

  <h2 id="considerations">Key Considerations</h2>

  <h3>Moving Between Countries</h3>
  <p>
    When you change your primary country of residence:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Stay within your coverage area and you're fine</li>
    <li>May need to notify insurer of the change</li>
    <li>Premiums may adjust based on new country</li>
    <li>Usually handled at renewal</li>
    <li>Some plans are more flexible than others</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Network Quality Varies</h3>
  <p>
    Global networks aren't equally strong everywhere:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Premium insurers (Bupa, Cigna) have strong networks in most regions</li>
    <li>Network may be weaker in less-developed countries</li>
    <li>Direct billing availability varies by country</li>
    <li>May need to pay and claim in some locations</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Time Zone and Service</h3>
  <p>
    Consider customer service accessibility:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>24/7 support is important for global coverage</li>
    <li>Multilingual support helpful when moving regions</li>
    <li>Telemedicine should work across time zones</li>
    <li>Premium insurers generally offer better global service</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Continuity of Care</h3>
  <p>
    When you move, consider:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Access to medical records across countries</li>
    <li>Continuing treatment started elsewhere</li>
    <li>Prescription transfers between countries</li>
    <li>Finding equivalent specialists in new location</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Can I change countries mid-year?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, within your coverage area. If you have worldwide coverage (excluding US), you can move from Spain to Thailand tomorrow without any changes to your policy. You may need to notify your insurer of your new primary residence.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I want to add US coverage later?</h3>
  <p>
    Most insurers allow this, typically at renewal. You'll go through some underwriting and premiums will increase significantly (50-100%). It's easier to include US from the start if you think you might need it.
  </p>

  <h3>Do I need to tell my insurer every time I travel?</h3>
  <p>
    No, not for travel within your coverage area. You only need to notify them when you change your primary country of residence—where you live most of the time. Short trips require no notification.
  </p>

  <h3>What happens if I'm hospitalized in a country with a weak network?</h3>
  <p>
    You pay upfront and submit for reimbursement. In countries where your insurer doesn't have direct billing arrangements, you'll need to pay the hospital and then claim the expenses back. Keep all documentation.
  </p>

  <h3>Is regional coverage enough if I travel occasionally outside my region?</h3>
  <p>
    Most regional plans include some coverage for travel outside your region—typically for trips up to 6 weeks. Check your specific plan terms. If you travel frequently outside your region, global coverage is safer.
  </p>

  <h3>Which insurer is best for digital nomads who change countries monthly?</h3>
  <p>
    For budget: SafetyWing—designed for nomads, no residence requirements. For full health: Cigna Global—excellent flexibility. For premium: Bupa Global—no restrictions on location.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This content is for informational purposes only. Coverage areas and flexibility vary by plan. We are not insurance brokers. Always verify coverage terms directly with insurers.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
